name: Brielle Guest House
address: Pecatu, South Kuta, Badung Regency, Bali 80361, Indonesia

review 2: What a treat. Excellent accommodation at very low price. I had very low expectations for this place but I‚Äôll be staying here every time I‚Äôm in this part of Bali. Staff is amazingly helpful and continually keep the place clean. Quiet location (I‚Äôd suggest having a scooter to get around or using grab). Fully equipped kitchen to do your own cooking. For the price you won‚Äôt find anything better.
review 3: I liked my stay although it is a bit far from everything but you can always book a gojek to go places. I was on the top floor and I liked it there, there is a terrace with lots of sunlight and views, somehow I felt very good those days. The staff doesn't speak English and it's a bit difficult to communicate.
review 4:
Good money to value.
Good internet, free  kitchen,towel,water, parking. Big rooftop could use some gym equipment or just a pulupbar. One toilet with a shower for 2 rooms of 16ppl can get crowded if fully booked. Not my case.
The gated community is very nice , with no special views, just a skeleton building close . üòÄ
Owerall a few days in a dorm here is totally ok . #MrBali83 approved üëå
review 5: Pretty poor quality place, I've been in better homestays throughout Bali. I stayed since the other options were too expensive. I had bugs crawling on the bed. And the location is inconvenient, since you must get a scooter to properly explore. The homestay looks like it's in a gated community away from the main street.

name: Rumah WJ Rooms and Suites
address: Sahadewa plaza, Pecatu, Kec. Kuta Sel., Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1:
Strange smell at the beginning and it was because of many naphthalene balls.

No hot water AT ALL

Air con was on and couldn‚Äôt be modified as the remote was faulty

No shower gels or shampoo

Towels, rooms, floor, beds sheets and many more things needs to be improved and cleaned

Helpful staff but very low condition of room

It‚Äôs cheap but bring your expectations to the lowest possible
review 2:
Stayed at this place twice, at the start of our trip in Bali and at the end to wrap things up. Was hosted by Om Alex, such a welcoming and friendly man who'd look out for you and give you some advices on where to go around Bali.

The first time we stayed, we had a room on the third floor. Loved this one. Simple, bright, (artificial light), large, and equipped with a cold AC. The second time, the room was on the second floor. Smaller room but still adequately spacious. Same cleanliness, brightness, and good temperature. Both times the hot water runs well, even in the sink. Furnitures like the wardrobe and hanging racks are available in the room too. Unfortunately, for both times, we weren't able to get a room with the balcony.

Another plus point is they have a refrigerator and drinkable water to refill your water bottle (the one on the 2nd floor tastes better than the one on the 1st).

Overall, it was a lovely stay. Will come back again if visiting Uluwatu.
review 3: Great value room in a good location 10 minute walk from the main street
review 4: Sleep and surf....rumah WJ rooms and suites....is the place to stay......ciaoooo
review 5: Very weird smell in the bathroom

name: Gracia Homestay
address: Perumahan Sahadewa, Jl. Griya Alam Pecatu No.1 Blok 0, Pecatu, Kec. Kuta Sel., Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1: I had a wonderful 3-week stay at Gracia Homestay. The staff were incredibly friendly and helpful, ensuring a comfortable experience with their great communication. The environment was pleasantly quiet and clean, and the location was perfect. I highly recommend Gracia Homestay and look forward to staying again in the near future!
review 2:
Gracia homestay was our home for 1 month. Amazing location with unique atmosphere: near the most beautiful beaches, shops, awesome road and big golf fields where you can walk or run. A lot of trees and beautiful views around, no noise, only nature.

Nice and clean rooms with AC and beautiful balcony, where you can watch sunsets. Big kitchen where you can cook everything you want. Nice swimming pool, not big but always clean.

Eli is a kindest woman and always ready to help you anytime! Highly recommend this place for stay!
review 3:
Thank you very much for the friendly welcome.
Close to the forest, clean air, amazing sunset views.
About 15 minutes to several beaches for surfing.
The room was clean as was the linens, towels and bathroom.
review 4: I have been living here for the second month and I really like everything. A chic area, a chic room and great sunset views. It is a beautiful, comfortable and safe place. Mrs. Ele is very responsive and kind, she takes care of her guests as her children and constantly treats durian with the fruits of a mandarin guava. This is the best place I've lived. The rooms are well cleaned and give clean towels. Thanks a lot, Ele.
review 5:
Brand new & very clean homestay,  owned by a really lovely Indonesian family. Your balcony will be overseeing a beautiful jungle. There's also a  cool rooftop for stargazing or sunset watching. Not right next to any stores or restaurants,  but once you have a scooter you'll be there in no time! Also 10-15 mins to all the nice beaches.
The building & area is still a work in progress,  since everything is so new, so it might look a bit empty at the moment, but I kinda like the peacefulness of that :)
Definitely recommended! Bring some ear plugs if you're a late & light sleeper (thin walls/doors), otherwise the place is really nice and quiet.

The atmosphere is also complemented by candles, pleasant music and an air-conditioned zoga.
